cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with text clustering, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), suggesting cs.CL and cs.IR as likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel active clustering algorithm, which involves machine learning and user interaction, indicating cs.LG and cs.AI as possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on clustering documents along dimensions such as sentiment, mood, gender, and age, which could fall under the scope of social and information sciences, suggesting cs.SI as a potential sub-category.
